.TH man 1 "13 Apr 2023" "1.0" "satori-cli man page"
.SH NAME
Satori CI is an automated testing platform that allows you to test throughout the software lifecycle.

.SH SYNOPSIS

satori-cli [category] [object] [action] [options]

.SH DESCRIPTION

.TP
\fBDashboard:\fR

satori-cli  dashboard                   \fBShows to user a dashboard with Repo information (Name, Status, etc).\fR  

.IP \fBConfig:\fR


satori-cli config token YOUR_TOKEN                             \fBSets user token.\fR 


.IP \fBRepository:\fR

satori-cli repo                                             \fBShows Repos dashboard.\fR 

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld                      --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld commits              --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld check-commits        --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld check-forks          --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld scan                 --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld scan-stop            --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld run                  --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld/commit123 run        --

satori-cli repo satoridev01/HelloWorld clean                --


.IP \fBMonitor:\fR

satori-cli monitor                      \fB tbc \fR 

satori-cli monitor ABC123               --

satori-cli monitor ABC123 start         --

satori-cli monitor ABC123 stop          --

satori-cli monitor ABC123 delete        --

.IP \fB**Report: /api/report/**\fR

satori-cli report                       --

satori-cli report DEF456                --

satori-cli report DEF456 output         --

satori-cli report DEF456 stop           --

satori-cli report DEF456 delete         --


.IP \fBRun:\fR

satori-cli run [path]                     \fBCreate report - tbc\fR 

satori-cli run playbook.yml         --

satori-cli run ./                   --


.IP \fBPlaybook:\fR

satori-cli playbook                     \fBShows to user playbook attributes [id, hash, url,etc.].\fR 

satori-cli playbook GHI456              --

satori-cli playbook GHI456 delete       --

.SH OPTIONS
The following options are available for Satori-CLI:

.TP
\fB--json\fR
Output results in JSON format.

.TP
\fB--filter\fR
Filter results using

